description._content: ID: B20056-25 Title: Untitled. Provenance: c.1650 Caption: Shah Jahan in durbar, holding a ruby in his right hand; 'chauri'-bearers stand on either side of him and an attendant before him holds a tray of jewels. On the left is Prince Alamgir (Aurangzeb) who salutes his father. The location is the Diwan-i-Am at Delhi Notes: Opaque watercolour.
